{2}-4AC}"></span>, called the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disc=
riminant" title=3D"Discriminant">discriminant</a> of the equation.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-14" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Conic_section#cite_note-14"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
Thus, the discriminant is <span class=3D"texhtml">=E2=88=92 4=CE=94</span> =
where <span class=3D"texhtml">=CE=94</span> is the <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Determinant" title=3D"Determinant">matrix determinant</a> =
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe=
-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xm=
lns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \left|=
