<ul><li>if <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>B</i><sup>2</sup> =E2=88=92 4<i>AC</i=
> &lt; 0</span>, the equation represents an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Ellipse" title=3D"Ellipse">ellipse</a>;
<ul><li>if <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>A</i> =3D <i>C</i></span> and <span c=
lass=3D"texhtml"><i>B</i> =3D 0</span>, the equation represents a <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Circle" title=3D"Circle">circle</a>, whic=
h is a special case of an ellipse;</li></ul></li>
<li>if <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>B</i><sup>2</sup> =E2=88=92 4<i>AC</i> =
=3D 0</span>, the equation represents a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Parabola" title=3D"Parabola">parabola</a>;</li>
<li>if <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>B</i><sup>2</sup> =E2=88=92 4<i>AC</i> &g=
t; 0</span>, the equation represents a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Hyperbola" title=3D"Hyperbola">hyperbola</a>;
<ul><li>if <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>A</i> + <i>C</i> =3D 0</span>, the eq=
uation represents a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rectangular_hy=
perbola" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Rectangular hyperbola">rectangular =
hyperbola</a>.</li></ul></li></ul>
<p>In the notation used here, <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-st=
yle:italic;">A</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:=
italic;">B</span> are polynomial coefficients, in contrast to some sources =
that denote the semimajor and semiminor axes as <span class=3D"texhtml mvar=
" style=3D"font-style:italic;">A</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" st=
yle=3D"font-style:italic;">B</span>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Invariants">Invariants</h4>=
</div>
<p>The discriminant <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>B</i><sup>2</sup> =E2=80=93 =
4<i>AC</i></span> of the conic section's quadratic equation (or equivalentl=
y the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Determinant" title=3D"Determ=
inant">determinant</a> <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>AC</i> =E2=80=93 <i>B</i>=
<sup>2</sup>/4</span> of the 2=E2=80=89=C3=97=E2=80=892 matrix) and the qua=
ntity <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>A</i> + <i>C</i></span> (the <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trace_(linear_algebra)" title=3D"Trace (linear =
algebra)">trace</a> of the 2=E2=80=89=C3=97=E2=80=892 matrix) are invariant=
 under arbitrary rotations and translations of the coordinate axes,<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-Protter_1970_326_15-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conic_section#cite_note-Protter_1970_326-15"><span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></s=
up><sup id=3D"cite_ref-16" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Conic_section#cite_note-16"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-17"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conic_section=
#cite_note-17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>16<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup> as is the determinant of the <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conic_section#Matrix_notation">3=E2=80=89=C3=97=E2=80=
=893 matrix above</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Spain_18-0" class=3D"reference"><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conic_section#cite_note-Spain-18"><=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup><sup class=3D"reference nowrap"><span title=3D"Page / location: p=
p. 60=E2=80=9362">:=E2=80=8App. 60=E2=80=9362=E2=80=8A</span></sup> The con=
stant term <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>F</i></span> and the sum <span class=
=3D"texhtml"><i>D</i><sup>2</sup> + <i>E</i><sup>2</sup></span> are invaria=
nt under rotation only.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Spain_18-1" class=3D"reference">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conic_section#cite_note-Spain-18">=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup><sup class=3D"reference nowrap"><span title=3D"Page / location: =
pp. 60=E2=80=9362">:=E2=80=8App. 60=E2=80=9362=E2=80=8A</span></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Eccentricity_in_terms_of_co=
efficients">Eccentricity in terms of coefficients</h4></div>
