</p><p>A <i>projective</i> mapping is a finite sequence of perspective mapp=
ings.
</p><p>As a projective mapping in a projective plane over a field (<a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pappian_plane" class=3D"mw-redirect" titl=
e=3D"Pappian plane">pappian plane</a>) is uniquely determined by prescribin=
g the images of three lines,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-57" class=3D"reference"><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conic_section#cite_note-57"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>53<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></su=
p> for the Steiner generation of a conic section, besides two points <span =
class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-=
mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D=
"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle U,V}">
